('Rescue P.C.I is done for which of the following?', 'Option C = Rescue P.C.I. After thrombolysis ST Elevation begin to reduce If ST Elevation persisting in spite of thrombolysis. So it\'s failure of thrombolysis | within 90 minutes Rescue PCI Types of PCI Primary PCI done for STEMI (Door to device time < 90 minutes). Delayed PCI done for Unstable Angina NSTEMI Rescue PCI Failure of thrombolysis (within 90 minutes).', 3, 'Persistent chest pain with ST elevation > 60 min after thrombolysis', 'Persistent chest pain with ST elevation > 30 min after thrombolysis', 'Persistent Chest pain with ST elevation >90 min after thrombolysis', 'Pain with ST elevation for >120minutes after thrombolysis', 'Medicine', 'Acute coronary syndrome', 'ffa5b47b-7d02-489f-9bcf-f6753b2be449', 3, 1, '66.67', 28),
('Fever associated with infection', 'Fever right shifts the oxygen dissociation curve, which allows for a greater release of oxygen to the tissue, making oxygen easily available to neutrophils and monocytes for use in the oxygen-dependent myeloperoxidase system of bactericidal killing. Having more oxygen available to tissue also enhances wound healing. In addition, fever interferes with bacterial and viral replication by providing a hostile environment for incubation. Fever is produced by the release of interleukin-I from macrophages. Interleukin-I, in turn, stimulates the hypothalamus to synthesize prostaglandins, which interact with the thermoregulatory center to produce fever.', 4, 'Accelerates bacterial and viral replication', 'Left shifts the oxygen dissociation curve', 'Is due to interleukin-1 released from CD4 T-helper cells', 'Increase oxygen release to tissue', 'Physiology', 'General physiology', 'fefb2a6d-129a-4ebd-9100-fcdb862c98a2', 59, 44, '25.42', 48),
('Last organ to putrefy in females is?', 'Ans. is \'b\' i.e., Uterus Order of putrefactiono Order of appearance of putrefaction from earliest to last is : larynx, trachea > stomach, intestine > spleen, liver > brain, lungs > heart > kidney, bladder > uterus/prostate > bone.o Amongst the soft tissues uterus in female and prostate in malesm are last to undergo putrefaction, as uterus and prostate resist putrefaction. Otherwise bones are last to undergo putrefaction, overall.', 2, 'Liver', 'Uterus', 'Brain', 'Breast', 'Forensic Medicine', 'Injuries', '8cf45c14-9de1-4f72-a51c-e0ab03cd4518', 7, 3, '57.14', 26),
