('Which is not an aryl phosphate -', 'Organophosphate poisoning is the most common poisoning in India followed by aluminium phosphide. Organophosphorus compounds are classified as 1. Alkyl compounds -- such as tetraethyl pyrophosphate (TEPP), hexa ethyl tetraphosphate (HETP), octa methyl pyrophosphate (OMPA), malathion etc. 2. Aryl compounds -- such as parathion, chlorothion, diazinon (Tik-20), paraoxon etc. REF;THE SYNOPSIS OF FORENSIC MEDICINE:KS NARAYANA REDDY;28th EDITION;PAGE NO 291', 3, 'Parathion', 'TIK-20', 'Malathion', 'Paraoxon', 'Forensic Medicine', 'Poisoning', '96952c56-c9f6-43f2-a638-122711492aa0', 31, 19, '38.71', 35),
